verbose_text: Interestingly, the IgM level was not significantly changed in B6-Il2rg-/- mice (wild type, 674 mug / muL; homozygote, 597.8 mug / muL; Fig. XREF_FIG f), and all immunoglobulin levels in B6-Il2rg-/- mice were the highest among those in the four immunodeficient mouse strains (IgG1, 3.6 mug / muL; IgG2a, 1.4 mug / muL; IgG2b, 3.7 mug / muL; IgG3, 586.8 mug / muL; IgA, 2.7 mug / muL; IgM, 597.8 mug / muL).
